Cormorant Garamond Light Regular (CormorantGaramond-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond Light'.

name

Mac NID 6

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'CormorantGaramond-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Cormorant Garamond Light Italic (CormorantGaramond-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CormorantGaramond-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Cormorant Garamond Medium Regular (CormorantGaramond-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CormorantGaramond-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

Cormorant Garamond Medium Regular (CormorantGaramond-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond Medium'.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CormorantGaramond-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Cormorant Garamond SemiBold Regular (CormorantGaramond-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond SemiBold'.

Cormorant Garamond SemiBold Italic (CormorantGaramond-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'CormorantGaramond-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Cormorant Garamond SemiBold Italic (CormorantGaramond-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Cormorant Garamond' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Cormorant Garamond SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Every PostScript name is fine.
